snippet.textDisplay:
I absolutely LOVE those greenhouses. I don't know how high-tech this one in Michigan is, but the best ones in Europe are even pressurized to have a higher atmospheric pressure inside. That way dust and insects cant get in through seals and opening in the greenhouse, and the inside is totally devoid of insects. There's absolutely no need for pesticides, and that grows a healthier, more natural product.
Sorry for the rant, absolutely geeking out about these things.
